Multiple motor accidents yesterday claimed one life and left four others injured in two locations at Ihiala and Uli, both in Ihiala Ihiala Local Council Area of Anambra State. A statement issued by the Sector Public Education officer of Federal Road Safety Commission Mrs. Florence N. Edor said the four vehicles had a fatal crash at Okija at about 0130hrs. According to the statement the vehicles involved included Mitsubishi bus with registration number RUM 495 AE whose driver had not been identified, a Man Diesel Truck with registration number UWN 262 XX, whose driver was also not identified, Mercedes Benz 190 with registration number NSH 32 FM and Land Rover jeep with registration AE 743 MNG. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! It said the accident occurred as a result of route violation. According to the report a total of 25 persons were on board the vehicles and they comprised of 21 male adults and four female adults. FCT Minister Commends Police Officers For Securing Abuja Nigerians Must Look Forward To Prosperous 2021 – Makinde Four male adults it said sustained varying degrees of injury and were taken to Osongwu hospital by Okija Divisional Police, while one male adult who was also taken to Osongwu hospital by Okija Division Police was confirmed dead by the Doctor on duty, and later deposited at the mortuary. Also at Uli, an unidentified driver of Toyota Hiace bus with registration number UKP 48 YP had a serious and lone crash along Uli road by Jehovah witness, Ihiala yesterday too. The report quoting eyewitnesses said that the crash was due to tyre Burst. It involved 14 persons on board comprising of eight male adults and four female adults. According to the report nine persons sustained injuries and was taken to Our Lady’s of Lourdes Hospital Ihiala and Vera Clinic Uli by FRSC rescue team from Ihiala. Based on these, the Sector Commander Corps Commander Andrew A Kumapayi commiserated with the injured and wished them accelerated recovery. He admonished motorist to avoid the use of expired tyres or tokunbo Tyres noting that crash can be avoided if motorist adhere to safety rules SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION